(This document summarizes the architecture, trade-offs, and operational plan for the Redemption microservice deployed on AWS EKS.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 12 Tf
72 660 Td
(1. Architecture: EKS cluster in 3 AZs with private API endpoint, ALB ingress, Aurora Multi-AZ, Redis, and SQS-based buffering.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 12 Tf
72 640 Td
(2. Scalability: HPA and Karpenter-driven autoscaling, queue depth metrics, and warm baseline replicas for zero downtime.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 12 Tf
72 620 Td
(3. Security: IRSA, least privilege IAM, network segmentation, private endpoints, and WAF shielding.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 12 Tf
72 600 Td
(4. Observability: Prometheus/Grafana, Fluent Bit logs, OpenTelemetry tracing, health probes, and automated rollback.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 12 Tf
72 580 Td
